        <h1>How the Cavs Defied the Odds with a Historic 3-1 Comeback</h1>
        <p>The most <b>memorable moment</b> in NBA history came in the famous comeback by the <b>Cleveland Cavaliers</b> in the <i>2016 NBA Finals</i> against the <i>Golden State Warriors</i>. The finals began on <b>June 2, 2016</b>. After trailing <b>3-1</b> in the series, the Cavaliers, with <b>LeBron James</b> and <b>Kyrie Irving</b>, won three in a row, setting them up to win their first NBA championship as a franchise. This was <i>historic</i> because <i>no team had ever come back from a <u>3-1 deficit</u> in the Finals before</i>. The series had it all <b>intensity, drama, and unforgettable performances</b>. LeBron James went on consecutive <b>41-point games</b> in Games 5 and 6. LeBron's <i>symbolic block</i> off the backboard was a defining moment. Kyrie Irving made one of the most <i>clutch plays in NBA history</i> a sidestep <b>three-pointer</b> over Stephen Curry (in his <i>grill</i>), sealing <i>Game 7</i>. The <i>Warriors</i>, who had set an <b>NBA record</b> with <u>73 regular-season wins</u>, saw their <u>historic season</u> end in <del>heartbreak</del>.</p>
